{"id":"math120-antideriv210-001","cid":"MATH 120","topic":"Antiderivatives and Integrals","subtopic":"Antiderivatives","difficulty":1,"license":"CC BY-NC-SA (Numberbender original)","instruction":"Find the antiderivative (indefinite integral): integral of {a}x^{n} dx.","params":{"a":{"type":"int","min":1,"max":6},"n":{"type":"int","min":1,"max":4}},"answer_expr":"antideriv210","steps":["Power rule for integration: integral of x^n dx = x^(n+1)/(n+1) + C.","integral of {a}x^{n} dx = ({a}/{n+1})x^{new_exp210} + C = {answer_antideriv210}x^{new_exp210} + C."],"tags":["survey-calculus","antiderivative","power-rule","indefinite-integral"]}
